Today, more than three years after the bombardment, little more is known than then, indeed the puzzles became rather larger with time.
Former U.S. President George W. Bush recently revealed in his memoirs that while the CIA was pretty sure before the attack that Syria was building a reactor in el-Kibar, it saw little evidence that there was “an active nuclear weapons program” in the country.
