Pakistan’s nuclear program raises major concerns in the US
Islamabad is producing nuclear weapons “faster than any other country.”
WikiLeaks revelations confirm ties between the Taliban and Pakistan.
The content of the correspondence between the North American Embassy in Pakistan and the US State Department, revealed by the Wikileaks internet portal, confirms the enormous concern of the Pakistani nuclear program Washington.
On the sidelines of the clarifying and juicy details offered by the documents on the content of the talks and the mindset of accredited North American diplomats in Islamabad, they reveal that cooperation between the two countries on nuclear security is not being strengthened, but on the contrary is “declining,” and that the unstable Asian country is producing more nuclear weapons “to a faster rhythm than any other country.”
