“Pakistan needs to hire strictly religious personnel to guard the nuclear facilities; because of the low educational and cultural level, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people who are involved in nuclear or missile programs,” said Yuri Korolev, a Russian foreign ministry expert, in a meeting with his North American counterparts.
